ec-scale radio\nemission, the time-averaged kinetic power of this outflow is estimated to be\n$Q\\approx1.5\\times10^{42}$ erg s$^{-1}$, which is typical of radio outflows in\nlow-luminosity AGN. This supports the idea that radio \"jets\" and outflowing\ncoronal winds are indistinguishable in Seyfert galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Dec 2014 10:05:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
